{"answer_label":"exclude-first-consolidation","answer":"Keep both outside the first consolidation. Agent Pantry brings browser-state capture, secrets, AES-GCM, and security coverage the target repository did not yet have; agent-notify's optional alert integration does not create a source-level dependency.","contradiction_caught":null,"contradiction_explanation":"","minority_finding":"agent-notify alone is low-risk because it is a small opt-in pure-Go adapter, but the decision concerns including both components.","evidence":["Agent Pantry handles cleartext browser storage state, long-lived secrets, and crypto framing.","Optional manifest-managed installation supports agent-notify without importing either repository."]}
